      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>kursarwa</w><w>aurtse</w><w>emparkre</w><w>orocceṃ</w><w>tsuwaiceṃ</w>
<w>bodhisa<lb corresp="#a2"/><supplied>tveṃts</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>wa</supplied>rñai</w><w>satyānuparivart</w><w>kaṃtwasa</w><w>vipaśyiṃ</w><w>śikhiṃ</w>
<w>viśva<lb corresp="#a3"/><supplied>bhūṃ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w>snai</w><w>olyapo</w><w>poyśiṃñeṣṣe</w><w>lantuṃñeś</w><w>abhiṣek</w>
<w>yā<lb corresp="#a4"/><supplied>moṣ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>tet</supplied>kāṣ</w><w>śpālmeṃ</w><w>pañäktäṃñe</w><w>perneṣṣe</w><w>vyākarit</w><w>kälpoṣ</w>
<lb corresp="#a5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ompalskoññe</supplied>ntane</w><w>āklyi</w><w>yāmoṣ</w><w>śtwāra</w><w>dhyananmameṃ</w><w>pīś</w>
<w>abhi<lb corresp="#b1"/><supplied>jñänta</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w>alaitacci</w><w>krentaunameṃ</w><w>śak</w><w>vaśitveṃññentasa</w><w>ka</w>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>späṃntaitsäṃñenta</w><w>śak</w><w>maiyyaṃ</w><w>se</w><w>ṣp</w><w>temeṃ</w><w>mante</w><w>śa</w>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>lkālñesa</w><w>warñai</w><w>toṃ</w><w>krentauna</w><w>källālñene</w><w>snai</w><w>sklok</w>
<lb corresp="#b4"/></p>
            <lg type="poem">
               <lg n="X" type="strophe">
                  <l n="x"><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣpä</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>cmelane</w><w>cmelñe</w><w>srūkalñe</w><pc>:</pc></l>
                  <l n="x"><w>lakäṣṣeñcaṃ</w>
<w>apā<lb corresp="#b5"/><supplied>kärtse</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/></l>
                  <l n="x"><w><supplied>e</supplied>r<supplied>e</supplied>patempa</w><pc>:</pc></l>
                  <l n="x"><w>tasemane</w><w>po</w><w>pīś</w><w>āntseṃ</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>tserekwa</w><w>ka</w><w>kärsoṣ</w><w>cai</w><pc>:</pc></l>
               </lg>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the wide [and] long (way?) of [many] leagues ... of the great [and] progressing bodhisattvas ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... with a tongue having truth as a consequence, starting with ..., Vipaśyin, Śikhin, Viśvabhū,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having acc(omplished) the consecration for the kingship without superior, pertaining to omniscience</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having received immediately the excellent prophecy pertaining to the rank of Buddha</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having studied in the (concentration), (having reached?) from the four visions the five supernatural know(ledges) </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... not having fallen away from virtues, through the ten demonstrations of power ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (with?) marks of self confidence, and the ones who, provided with ten powers, following that ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... without doubt in the obtaining of these virtues starting with seeing ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... and the rebirth [and] the death in the [five forms of] existences; showing evidently</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... these ones have understood all the five skandhas comparable to the form as deception </seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="lingcomment">We have some late forms: two times a nominative plural in <hi>-an</hi> instead of <hi>-añ</hi> (b2, b4) and the relative pronoun <hi>se</hi> for <hi>k<hi rend="subscript">u</hi>se</hi> (b2). The former is in accordance with the unusual spelling of geminate <hi>-ññ-</hi> by <hi>-ṃñ-</hi> pointing to a genuine depalatalization in the TB variety of the scribe, with <hi>-ṃñ-</hi> being a somewhat artificial orthography.</note><note type="philcomment">In b4 a meter of 15 syllables seems to start; the text before seems to be prose.</note><note type="philcomment">The use of anusvāra is remarkable; often we find redundant anusvāra and also anusvāra before palatal nasal instead of palatal geminate.</note><note type="remarks">Might belong to the same manuscript as <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkns112"/>.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="lingcomment">The adjective <hi>tsuwaits(ts)e</hi> is based on the adverb <hi>tsuwai</hi> ‘towards, up to’, so that it may refer to the progress of the bodhisattvas in their career.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">It seems that <hi>tasemane</hi> has to be constructed with the preceding comitative <hi>erepatempa</hi> even though this belongs to a different pāda.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p><label>other</label>Quoted in <bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1954"/><citedRange>82</citedRange></bibl><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1948"/><citedRange>329</citedRange></bibl>..</p>
            <p><label>Photo</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:windekens1940"/></bibl>: pl. I-II.</p>
         </div>
